      'The exclusion of persons with certain disabilities from eligibility for jury service under the Juries Act 1976 was challenged under Article 40.1 on the basis that it discriminated against persons with disabilities in their entitlement to participate in a civic institution. The High Court examined whether the exclusion was rationally justified by reference to the functional requirements of jury service or whether it constituted an impermissible discrimination. The case is an early engagement by the Irish courts with disability as a ground of equality analysis under Article 40.1.',
