      'The denial of the one-parent family payment to bereaved fathers who were not living alone with their children violated the equality guarantee in Article 40.1. The Supreme Court held that bereaved fathers and bereaved mothers were in materially comparable situations, and that the differential treatment \u2014 rooted in historical assumptions about gender roles \u2014 could not be justified under a modern constitutional equality analysis. The decision is the most significant Irish equality ruling of 2024 and confirms that historically entrenched gender-based distinctions in social welfare law require compelling justification.',
