    legal_principle:
      "The denial of the widowed parent's allowance to an unmarried bereaved parent was held to violate Article 14 ECHR (read with Article 1 Protocol 1) by the UK Supreme Court, which found that the differential treatment of cohabiting parents compared to married parents in respect of bereavement benefits was not justifiable. The decision is directly relevant to the reasoning of the Irish Supreme Court in Donnelly [2022] and O'Meara [2024] and represents a closely parallel ECHR analysis of the same social welfare equality issue.",
