    legal_principle:
      'The Constitution protects unenumerated personal rights under Article 40.3, including a right to marital privacy. The Court held that a married woman had a constitutional right to import contraceptives for personal use within marriage. This right, though not expressly stated, was implied from the nature of the marital relationship as protected by Article 41.',
