      'Irish citizens enjoy a constitutional right to privacy as an unenumerated right under Article 40.3. The unlawful tapping of telephone lines by An Garda S\u00edoch\u00e1na, without legal authority, constitutes a breach of that right. The State is obliged to defend and vindicate this right against unjustified interference by public authorities.',
