      'The right to silence and the privilege against self-incrimination are unenumerated personal rights protected by Article 40.3 of the Constitution. However, these rights are not absolute and may be restricted by the Oireachtas where proportionate to a legitimate aim. The proportionality test requires that restrictions impair the constitutional right as little as reasonably possible.',
