    legal_principle:
      'There is no constitutional right to assisted suicide under the Irish Constitution. Article 40.3.2, which obliges the State to protect the right to life, imposes a positive duty on the State inconsistent with facilitating or permitting assistance with dying. The right to life under the Constitution does not incorporate a corollary right to die with assistance.',
