    legal_principle:
      'An accused person charged with a serious criminal offence has an unenumerated constitutional right to free legal aid where they cannot afford legal representation and where the interests of justice require it. This right derives from Article 38.1 (trial in due course of law) and the guarantee of equality under Article 40.1, read alongside the general right to fair procedures.',
