      'Article 41 protects the rights of the family as a unit, including the right of spouses to cohabit. However, the State retains sovereign power to control immigration and may deport a non-national spouse where justified by legitimate immigration concerns. The constitutional right of the family must be balanced against this sovereign power using a proportionality analysis that considers all relevant circumstances.',
