    legal_principle:
      "A plaintiff seeking to challenge the constitutionality of a statutory provision must demonstrate a sufficient personal interest in the matter \u2014 locus standi requires that the plaintiff's own rights or interests have been, or are at risk of being, adversely affected by the impugned provision. A plaintiff may not ordinarily challenge a law on the basis that it affects the rights of third parties who are not before the court.",
