      "Article 42 recognises the rights and duties of parents as the primary educators of their children. A pre-marriage agreement between the parents of a mixed-religion marriage regarding the religious upbringing of children is enforceable by the courts. The father cannot unilaterally resile from such an agreement to the detriment of the mother's rights and the agreement's purpose.",
