      "In considering the deportation of a non-national who is part of a family with constitutional rights under Article 41, the decision-maker must carry out a genuine proportionality exercise that weighs the constitutional family rights against the State's interest in immigration control. A failure to engage adequately with the constitutional dimension will render the deportation order unlawful.",
