      'A statutory levy that interferes with the constitutional right to property under Article 43 must be proportionate to a legitimate aim and must not impose an excessive or arbitrary burden. The court will subject fiscal legislation to constitutional scrutiny where it is alleged to constitute a disproportionate or irrational interference with property rights, though a degree of deference is afforded to the Oireachtas in matters of fiscal and economic policy.',
