      'The principles of natural justice \u2014 the right to be heard and the rule against bias \u2014 apply to administrative decision-making bodies that determine rights or interests of individuals. A person whose rights or legitimate expectations are adversely affected by an administrative decision is entitled to fair procedures before that decision is made, including adequate notice of the case against them and a reasonable opportunity to respond.',
