      "The constitutional right to trial by jury under Article 38.5 and the protection against double jeopardy are fundamental rights, but they do not preclude the prosecution from bringing an appeal against a directed acquittal in the Circuit Court by way of case stated. There is no constitutional right on the part of an accused person to have a directed acquittal stand if it was made in error; the prosecution's right of appeal in such limited circumstances is consistent with the Constitution.",
