      'The Article 26 procedure may be used to test the constitutionality of legislation dealing with cross-border criminal jurisdiction. The Supreme Court upheld the Bill as constitutional, affirming the Oireachtas power to legislate for offences committed outside the State in certain circumstances. The judgment recognised principles of comity between states as relevant to the exercise of extraterritorial criminal jurisdiction.',
