      "The Oireachtas has a wide discretion in the reorganisation of electoral constituencies, provided that the resulting arrangements comply with the constitutional requirements for proportional representation and broadly equal voting power. The Supreme Court upheld the Electoral (Amendment) Bill 1983 as constitutional, affirming the legislature's discretion in drawing constituency boundaries.",
