      'Retrospective legislation which imposes financial liability for charges that were unlawfully collected from individuals constitutes an unjust attack on the property rights of those individuals and is repugnant to the Constitution. The Supreme Court found the Health (Amendment) (No. 2) Bill 2004 to be repugnant to Article 40.3, making it one of only a handful of Bills found unconstitutional under Article 26.',
