      'The constitutional protection of the dwelling under Article 40.5 applies to searches conducted pursuant to immigration and security legislation as it does to searches under general criminal law; the Garda National Immigration Bureau does not enjoy any wider search powers than those subject to constitutional warrant requirements. A search of a dwelling pursuant to immigration powers must be authorised by a constitutionally valid warrant issued by an independent authority.',
