    legal_principle:
      'The inviolability of the dwelling guaranteed by Article 40.5 requires that any search warrant authorising entry into a private home must have been issued by an authority that has genuinely and independently applied its mind to whether the warrant should issue; a judicial officer who merely rubber-stamps a warrant application without exercising genuine independent judgment does not satisfy the constitutional requirement for independent oversight of search authorisation.',
