      'Article 16 of the Constitution requires that D\u00e1il constituencies be revised periodically to maintain, as far as practicable, the ratio of members to population across all constituencies, but it does not impose a requirement of strict mathematical equality. The Supreme Court confirmed that the Oireachtas retains a reasonable margin of discretion in drawing constituency boundaries and that the constitutional standard is one of reasonable approximation to equality rather than perfect proportionality. An electoral scheme will only be unconstitutional where it departs so substantially from the required ratio as to amount to a breach of the principle of proportional representation guaranteed by Article 16.',
