      "Article 16.2 of the Constitution requires that D\u00e1il constituency boundaries be drawn so as to produce, as far as practicable, an equal ratio of members to population, but mathematical equality is neither required nor achievable, and the Oireachtas is afforded a margin of appreciation in implementing this constitutional directive. The Supreme Court, applying the principles from O'Donovan and Kelly, confirmed that slight deviations from strict mathematical equality do not invalidate a constituency revision where those deviations result from the legitimate exercise of the Oireachtas's discretion to balance competing constitutional and practical considerations.",
