      'The constitutional right to vote in D\u00e1il elections is a fundamental right of citizens, and the Oireachtas may impose reasonable procedural requirements as conditions of the exercise of that right, provided such requirements do not amount to a disproportionate restriction on the franchise. The High Court affirmed that restrictions on voting rights must have a rational basis connected to the proper administration of elections and must not be so burdensome as to effectively disenfranchise significant categories of citizens without constitutional justification.',
