    legal_principle:
      'Article 40.4 of the Constitution guarantees the right of every person to apply to the High Court for an inquiry into the legality of their detention, and the courts must give effect to this guarantee by conducting a full and effective review of the grounds of detention. The Supreme Court confirmed that the scope of an Article 40.4 inquiry is not confined to purely formal defects in the warrant of commitment but extends to any ground that goes to the fundamental legality of the detention, including constitutional grounds, and that the court must be satisfied that the detention is in accordance with law before declining to order the release of the applicant.',
