      'The constitutional guarantee of personal liberty in Article 40.4 extends to persons detained under mental health legislation, and the courts may inquire into the legality of psychiatric detention by way of habeas corpus where the statutory procedures for detention have not been properly followed or where the detention is not justified by the criteria established by law. The Supreme Court confirmed that the right to liberty guaranteed by Article 40.4 is not diminished by the fact that a person is detained for medical rather than penal reasons, and that the protections of the constitutional guarantee apply fully to persons held under mental health law.',
