    legal_principle:
      "The Supreme Court held that constitutional fair procedures \u2014 including the right to a fair hearing and the principle of audi alteram partem \u2014 apply to decisions made by private professional bodies when those bodies exercise functions of a public nature, particularly where their decisions may affect a person's livelihood, reputation, or ability to practise a profession. The court affirmed that the reach of constitutional justice is not confined to courts and statutory tribunals but extends to any body exercising significant public power over individuals, including bodies incorporated or operating under statutory authority. The constitutional requirement of fair procedures cannot be excluded or reduced by contract alone where the decision-making body exercises quasi-public functions.",
