    legal_principle:
      "The Supreme Court of Canada struck down the common law rule permitting the Crown to raise the issue of insanity over an accused's objection as a violation of s.7 of the Charter (right to liberty and security of the person in accordance with the principles of fundamental justice), and then applied the remedy of reading-in \u2014 adding words to the Criminal Code to preserve the verdict of not guilty by reason of insanity as an available defence \u2014 combined with a suspended declaration of invalidity to allow Parliament time to enact conforming legislation. The case is a significant authority on the combination of reading-in and suspended declarations as complementary remedial tools following a finding of unconstitutionality.",
