    legal_principle:
      'The UK Supreme Court held that the exclusion of lone fathers from child tax credit entitlement on the same basis as lone mothers did not violate Article 14 ECHR read with Article 1 of Protocol 1, finding that the differential treatment of one-parent families had a legitimate aim and a reasonable justification, and giving useful guidance on the approach to sex discrimination in the context of welfare benefits administered by reference to primary caring responsibility. The case illustrates how Article 14 ECHR operates in welfare contexts involving gender and parental status and has been cited in comparative Irish equality proceedings concerning the differential treatment of unmarried fathers and the constitutional rights of lone parent families.',
