    court: 'Supreme Court of Ireland',
    jurisdiction: 'IE',
    legal_principle:
      'The Supreme Court established the foundational principle that all Acts of the Oireachtas must be presumed to be constitutional unless the contrary is clearly established, and that where a statutory provision is reasonably capable of two interpretations \u2014 one of which is consistent with the Constitution and one of which is not \u2014 the court must adopt the constitutional interpretation. The Court further held that the Constitution must be construed as a whole and that individual provisions are to be read in light of the general constitutional order and the values it enshrines. This case is the definitive Irish authority on the presumption of constitutionality and the principle of constitutional construction of statutes.',
