      'Costello J held that the constitutional guarantee of freedom of expression in Article 40.6.1\u00b0(i) of Bunreacht na h\u00c9ireann encompasses a broader constitutional right to communicate \u2014 as an implied or unenumerated right under Article 40.3 \u2014 and that a statutory monopoly on postal services that prevented private operators from conveying letters interfered with this constitutionally protected right to communicate. The case is a foundational authority on the unenumerated right to communicate as a personal right under Article 40.3 and on the constitutional limits of State monopolies in the communications sector.',
