      'The High Court held that the constitutional guarantee of freedom of expression in Article 40.6.1\u00b0(i) of Bunreacht na h\u00c9ireann extends to commercial speech and broadcasting, and that the exercise of regulatory powers over broadcasting by the Independent Radio and Television Commission (IRTC) is subject to constitutional review to ensure that licensing decisions do not unjustifiably restrict the constitutional right to communicate and the freedom of expression. The case confirmed that constitutional rights are engaged in the licensing of broadcast media and that administrative bodies exercising statutory discretion in this field must do so in a constitutionally compliant manner.',
