      'The Supreme Court held that the constitutional guarantee of the family in Article 41 of Bunreacht na h\u00c9ireann is confined to the family based on marriage, and that the succession and property rights arising on the death of a married person do not automatically extend to the non-marital partner of the deceased, notwithstanding any personal or financial contribution the partner may have made during the relationship. The Court confirmed that while the State may by legislation confer rights on non-marital families, the constitutional guarantee in Article 41 does not of itself require such extension, and the distinction between marital and non-marital families \u2014 while significant \u2014 was not at that time constitutionally impermissible under Article 40.1.',
