    legal_principle:
      "The Supreme Court extended the exclusionary rule established in Weeks to cover not only directly seized evidence but also derivative evidence \u2014 that is, evidence obtained as an indirect result of an unconstitutional search or seizure. Justice Holmes articulated the 'fruit of the poisonous tree' doctrine, holding that if the tree is poisoned, its fruits are equally tainted. The government cannot use the fact of an illegal search as a basis to demand production of the very materials it unconstitutionally viewed.",
