    legal_principle:
      'The Supreme Court extended the good faith exception to the Fourth Amendment exclusionary rule to cases where police conduct a search in objectively reasonable reliance on binding appellate precedent that is later overruled. Because the deterrence rationale for the exclusionary rule is absent where officers act in compliance with then-authoritative legal guidance, suppression of evidence in such circumstances produces no deterrent benefit while imposing substantial costs on the truth-seeking function of criminal trials.',
