    legal_principle:
      'The Supreme Court held that a state prisoner cannot seek federal habeas corpus review of a Fourth Amendment exclusionary rule claim where the state has provided a full and fair opportunity to litigate the claim at trial and on direct appeal. The majority reasoned that the incremental deterrent effect of applying the exclusionary rule on collateral review is outweighed by the substantial costs imposed on the administration of justice, thereby confining the exclusionary rule to its core function of deterrence and acknowledging that it is not a guarantee of accurate fact-finding.',
