    legal_principle:
      'The Supreme Court of Canada held that an individual retains a constitutionally protected reasonable expectation of privacy in their home under section 8 of the Canadian Charter of Rights and Freedoms, and that a warrantless search of a dwelling-house \u2014 even where police seek to justify the entry on ostensible consent or exigent circumstances \u2014 will ordinarily constitute a serious Charter breach requiring exclusion of evidence under section 24(2) following the Grant analysis.',
