      "Article 42A.1, inserted by the Thirty-First Amendment of the Constitution, confers independent constitutional rights on children that are not derivative of parental rights and must be vindicated by the State in its own right. The Child and Family Agency, in exercising its statutory functions under the Child Care Act 1991, must act in conformity with the constitutional framework established by Article 42A. Care orders engaging the removal of a child from the family home engage the child's constitutional rights directly and must satisfy a proportionality test, requiring the State to demonstrate that the interference is necessary, proportionate, and in the best interests of the child.",
