      "Article 40.5 of the Constitution, which declares the dwelling of every citizen to be inviolable and incapable of being forcibly entered save in accordance with law, confers a constitutional right on the occupant that is capable of being vindicated by the courts. Entry into and search of a dwelling by Garda\u00ed without a valid warrant or other lawful authority constitutes a breach of the occupant's constitutional right under Article 40.5, and evidence obtained through such an unlawful entry may be excluded on constitutional grounds. The protection of Article 40.5 applies to the home as a place of particular constitutional sanctity and is not displaced merely because the occupant is suspected of criminal activity.",
