    legal_principle:
      "The Supreme Court upheld the constitutional validity of trial by judge alone in complex fraud cases pursuant to section 9 of the Criminal Justice Act 1999. Article 38.5 of the Constitution guarantees the right to trial by jury, but the Court confirmed that this right is not absolute and may be departed from in particular categories of case, including complex financial crime, where an accused elects for non-jury trial or where a judicial direction is made. The proportionality of permitting judge-alone trials in complex fraud was held to serve a legitimate constitutional objective and did not impermissibly infringe Article 38.5. The decision is significant as it confirmed the legislature's power to provide for non-jury trial in circumstances involving the complexity and length that would make a jury trial impractical.",
