      "The Supreme Court held that local authorities owe a statutory duty to provide Traveller accommodation and that systematic failure to discharge that duty engages constitutional equality protections under Article 40.1 and the State's obligations under Article 8 ECHR as applied through the European Convention on Human Rights Act 2003. The Court confirmed that the Irish Human Rights and Equality Commission may intervene in proceedings as amicus curiae to advance equality arguments, and that the courts must give effect to equality and non-discrimination norms in adjudicating on the rights of Travellers, who are a recognised ethnic group in Irish law.",
