      'The Supreme Court held that restrictions on access to environmental information, imposed under the European Communities (Access to Information on the Environment) Regulations, must be interpreted narrowly and in a manner consistent with both the constitutional right to freedom of expression and information under Article 40.6.1 and EU law obligations. The Court confirmed that access to information held by public bodies is a constitutionally protected interest where it forms part of the right to free expression, and that statutory exceptions to disclosure must be proportionate, clearly defined, and not applied in a manner that unduly burdens that right.',
