      "The right to travel is an unenumerated personal right protected by Article 40.3 of the Constitution, and any restriction on an Irish citizen's entitlement to a passport \u2014 which is the essential document enabling the exercise of that right \u2014 must be proportionate, lawfully grounded, and subject to judicial review.",
