      'The Supreme Court held that the principles of constitutional justice \u2014 including the right to be heard (audi alteram partem) and the right to an unbiased decision-maker (nemo iudex in causa sua) \u2014 apply with full force to administrative decisions made by statutory bodies exercising public powers, and that a breach of those principles will render an impugned decision unlawful and liable to be quashed. The Court also confirmed that legitimate expectation is a cognisable constitutional principle that may arise from clear representations by public authorities and that its breach is a ground for judicial review.',
