    legal_principle:
      'The High Court dismissed a constitutional challenge by Ryanair to emergency travel restriction regulations introduced in response to the COVID-19 pandemic, holding that the regulations constituted a proportionate and constitutionally justified limitation on the right to earn a livelihood under Article 40.3 and on personal liberty under Article 40.4. The Court applied the proportionality test as formulated in Heaney v. Ireland, finding that the restrictions pursued a legitimate aim \u2014 the protection of public health and life \u2014 and that the means employed were rationally connected to that aim, impaired the relevant rights as little as reasonably possible, and achieved a fair balance between the rights of the individual and the interests of the community. The case affirms the wide margin of appreciation afforded to the executive in genuine public health emergencies in the context of constitutional rights review.',
