    legal_principle:
      'The Supreme Court struck down provisions of the Industrial Relations (Amendment) Act 2012 conferring power on Joint Labour Committees and the Labour Court to set minimum pay and conditions for employment sectors, holding that the Oireachtas had unconstitutionally delegated its exclusive law-making power under Article 15.2.1 by failing to define the principles and policies governing the exercise of that power with sufficient precision. The Court affirmed and applied the principles-and-policies test for the constitutional validity of delegated legislation, holding that the Oireachtas must itself determine the essential policy choices and cannot confer on an administrative body or committee an effectively unlimited power to make binding norms regulating important constitutional rights.',
