      'The High Court held that the constitutional principles of natural and constitutional justice \u2014 including the right to be heard (audi alteram partem) and the right to know the case to be met (nemo iudex in causa sua) \u2014 apply to disciplinary proceedings conducted by voluntary and charitable organisations, not merely to statutory or public bodies, where those proceedings affect the employment rights or other constitutionally significant interests of the person concerned. An employee or member of a voluntary organisation who faces dismissal or other serious sanction is entitled to the constitutional minimum of fair procedures before any adverse decision is taken.',
