      "The High Court granted an injunction restraining student union officers from distributing information about abortion services available in other EU Member States, holding that such distribution was contrary to Article 40.3.3 of the Irish Constitution as it assisted in the destruction of the life of the unborn. The case was also referred to the Court of Justice of the European Union, which held that abortion services constituted 'services' within the meaning of what is now Article 56 TFEU, but that the restriction on student unions in this case did not fall within EU law because the students were not acting in a commercial or economic relationship with the abortion service providers in the United Kingdom.",
