    legal_principle:
      "In this companion case to DPP v. Smyth [2024] IESC 22, the Supreme Court confirmed and applied the same JC balancing analysis to telephone traffic and location data obtained under post-Digital Rights Ireland Irish data retention legislation. The Court held that the evidence was admissible despite the underlying statutory framework's subsequent incompatibility with EU law, because An Garda S\u00edoch\u00e1na had acted in good faith reliance on apparently valid domestic authority. The prosecution's interest in securing convictions for serious criminal offences outweighed any systemic benefit from exclusion. The case consolidates DPP v. Smyth [2024] IESC 22 and is the companion leading 2024 authority governing the admissibility of communications data in Irish criminal trials.",
