    court: 'Supreme Court of Ireland',
    jurisdiction: 'IE',
    legal_principle:
      "The Supreme Court held that Article 15.10 of the Constitution confers absolute immunity from civil suit in respect of utterances made in either House of the Oireachtas, and that this immunity extends to the conduct of committee hearings. Angela Kerins's claim for damages arising from her treatment by the Public Accounts Committee was therefore precluded by the constitutional guarantee of parliamentary privilege, regardless of whether malice or bad faith could be demonstrated on the part of committee members. The separation of powers requires that the internal regulation of parliamentary proceedings \u2014 including the conduct of committees \u2014 remains exclusively a matter for the Oireachtas itself under Article 15; any remedy lies with the legislature to reform its own procedures, not with the courts.",
