    full_summary:
      "Angela Kerins, the former CEO of Rehab Group, sought damages from D\u00e1il \u00c9ireann and the State arising from her treatment during a series of Public Accounts Committee (PAC) hearings in 2014. She had appeared voluntarily before the PAC and alleged that she was subjected to aggressive, unfair, and damaging questioning that caused serious harm to her health and reputation. Her claim raised the central question of whether the constitutional immunity afforded by Article 15.10 \u2014 which provides that members of the Oireachtas shall not be amenable to any court in respect of any utterance in either House \u2014 extended to bar civil liability arising from the conduct of committee proceedings. The Supreme Court held that it did. The Court reasoned that giving civil courts jurisdiction to examine the motive or adequacy of parliamentary utterances \u2014 even under the guise of assessing good faith \u2014 would constitute an unacceptable judicial encroachment on the autonomy of the legislature. Parliamentary privilege is absolute under Article 15.10. The Court acknowledged the seriousness of Ms Kerins's experience but held that the remedy was institutional, not judicial: the Oireachtas must itself reform its committee procedures to ensure witnesses are treated with fairness and dignity. The case is the definitive modern authority on the scope of parliamentary privilege in Irish constitutional law.",
