      "The Supreme Court held that Article 42A of the Constitution \u2014 which guarantees the rights of children as a distinct constitutional class \u2014 imposes an independent obligation on the Minister for Justice to assess and address the rights and best interests of a child who will be affected by a deportation decision, separate from and in addition to any assessment of the family unit's rights under Article 41. A failure to engage specifically with the child's Article 42A rights constitutes a fatal flaw in the deportation decision and renders it amenable to certiorari. Article 42A operates as a standalone constitutional imperative in the immigration context and cannot be subsumed within the Article 41 family rights analysis.",
